No, the authors do not include complete proofs of all theoretical results. The focus of the methods section is on introducing the human-centered evaluation framework for explainability methods and describing the Utility metric to evaluate the usefulness of these methods. The authors provide definitions and concepts for these methods, but they do not present any formal theorems or complete proofs to support theoretical results.
